possibly a 15% reduction from 1.61 values, and (since they seem tied together) a 15% boost foe Mercs/BM from 1.61 values.  At the very least reduce the nerf to the point where zerks can take on a main tank, as Mythic has stated we should be able to do, and as testing on Pend has shown we CANNOT.  If the damage stays the same, perhaps reduce the amount the damage is reduced due to dual wielding (i.e. the &quot;damage is halved to start, but goes up somewhat as LA spec does&quot;)<br>
<br>
2.Since damage is so much lower, get the endurance cost of left axe styles reduced (if we go with the 15% reduction mentioned above, ignore this one)<br>
<br>
3.Get defensive penalties removed from frenzy, since BMs/Mercs abilities have been boosted, have no disadvantages, and are on the same timer.  Example being Triple-Wield:On a 7 minute timer, same as frenzy.  Adds 50% to damage (base damage,not styled, exact amount is in dispute), similar to  frenzy (1-99% crits averages out to 50%).  BM is immune to crits, zerk loses evade, parry, and a chunk of AF.  Hmmmm.  Also, get duration increased from 20 secs to 30 secs, as BMs/Mercs abilities are 30 secs.<br>
<br>
4.Get Aurora Borealis swutched back to it's original form, since, with the RvR parry fix, it would be incredibly useful now, instead of an almost useless tail end of a 3 style rear positional chain.<br>
<br>
5.Possibly add flurry, which was added to BMs/Mercs to compensate for their low damage.  Assuming the damage stays as it is., if they enable zerks to actually take on main tanks, forget this one.<br>
<br>
6.Making our LA detaunt an anytime style instead of third in a chain, which is ridiculous. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ulfhednar1>Ulfhednar1</A> at: 5/28/03 9:08:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kethryndc>Kethryn DC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#000000>(5/3/03 5:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What I think the priorities should be for our TL</span><hr size=1> Sounds good there.<br>
